01:51.600 --> 01:55.920
Empirical just means knowable by observation or experience.

01:55.920 --> 01:58.240
Another term for this is a posteriori.

01:58.240 --> 02:01.520
And the point of this story is just that what this woman learns

02:01.520 --> 02:05.120
at the end of the conversation is not linguistic.

02:05.120 --> 02:08.160
She's not learning anything about the meaning of the name Jay-Z.

02:08.160 --> 02:09.360
She already knew that name.

02:09.920 --> 02:13.520
She's learning an empirical fact, a fact about the world,

02:13.520 --> 02:17.440
which is, oh, this guy that I've been sitting next to, he is Jay-Z.

02:18.240 --> 02:21.680
Consider these two sentences.

02:21.680 --> 02:27.040
Sean Carter is Sean Carter and Sean Carter is Jay-Z.

02:27.040 --> 02:31.600
That's Jay-Z's government name, his regular name.

02:31.600 --> 02:33.040
Sean Carter, that's his name.

02:33.040 --> 02:36.240
