have different modes of presentation,

15:14.400 --> 15:16.720
that sentence, the sentence that

15:16.720 --> 15:19.280
the point of intersection of A and B

15:19.280 --> 15:22.560
is the same as the point of intersection of B and C,

15:22.560 --> 15:25.360
that sentence, like sentence two here,

15:25.360 --> 15:28.400
can contain real genuine information,

15:28.400 --> 15:30.320
true knowledge, as Frege calls it.

15:30.320 --> 15:32.080
In our example, accordingly,

15:32.080 --> 15:33.760
the reference of the expressions

15:33.760 --> 15:35.600
the point of intersection of A and B

15:35.600 --> 15:37.840
and the point of intersection of B and C

15:37.840 --> 15:40.320
would be the same, but not their senses.

15:40.320 --> 15:44.320
Right, so these two names have the same referent,

15:44.320 --> 15:46.240
but different senses,

15:46.240 --> 15:48.480
different ways of presenting that referent.

15:48.480 --> 15:51.360
That's exactly what's going on with Sean Carter and Jay-Z.

15:51.360 --> 15:55.040
These two names, they refer to the same guy,

15:55.040 --> 15:56.480
they have the same referent,

15:56.480 --> 15:58.320
but they have different senses.

15:58.320 --> 16:00.880
They present him in different ways.

16:00.880 --> 16:02.800
And it's the same way with the example

16:02.800 --> 16:04.800
of the morning star and the evening star.

16:04.800 --> 16:07.360
The referent of evening star would be the same

16:07.360 --> 16:09.840
as that of morning star, but not the sense.

16:09.840 --> 16:13.520
So those two names, the morning star and the evening star,

16:13.520 --> 16:15.280
they have the same referent,

16:15.280 --> 16:16.640
which happens to be Venus,

16:16.640 --> 16:19.360
but they present that referent differently.

16:19.360 --> 16:23.600
They make reference to Venus via different senses.

16:23.600 --> 16:26.240
And this theory, this theory that says

16:26.240 --> 16:28.480
that for all the linguistic signs,

16:28.480 --> 16:30.400
there are two levels of meaning,

16:30.400 --> 16:32.640
the level of sense and the level of reference.

16:32.720 --> 16:36.160
This theory can explain both of these facts

16:36.160 --> 16:38.320
about identity statements like two.

16:38.320 --> 16:41.200
It can explain why these sentences are informative

16:41.200 --> 16:43.280
and it can explain why that information

16:43.280 --> 16:45.520
can be non-linguistic and empirical.

16:45.520 --> 16:47.200
It's possible for one to already know

16:47.200 --> 16:49.360
the linguistic information.

16:49.360 --> 16:53.040
One knows the sense of Sean Carter, the meaning.

16:53.040 --> 16:57.360
And one knows the sense of the term or name Jay-Z.

16:57.360 --> 17:00.080
But then one can find out, oh!

17:00.080 --> 17:01.040
Oh!

17:01.040 --> 17:04.080
These two terms that I already know the meaning to,

17:04.080 --> 17:06.320
they refer to the very same guy.

17:06.320 --> 17:08.320
That is how Frege solves the puzzle.

17:08.320 --> 17:10.560
Oh, but there's more, there's like way more.

17:10.560 --> 17:13.280
The regular connection between a sign, its sense

17:13.280 --> 17:15.200
and its referent is of such a kind

17:15.200 --> 17:18.080
that to the sign, there corresponds a definite sense

17:18.080 --> 17:20.560
and to that, in turn, a definite referent.

17:20.560 --> 17:22.880
The point Frege is making there is just that

17:22.880 --> 17:27.200
in the normal case, for one name, there is one sense

17:27.200 --> 17:30.000
and then one referent, one to one to one.

17:30.080 --> 17:32.560
While to a given referent, an object,

17:32.560 --> 17:35.040
there does not belong only a single sign.

17:35.040 --> 17:38.480
But if instead we start with the object, the referent,

17:38.480 --> 17:41.600
there might be more than one name for that object, right?

17:41.600 --> 17:44.640
There might be Jay-Z and Sean Carter and Hove.

17:45.200 --> 17:46.480
That's another one, I think.

17:46.480 --> 17:48.720
The same sense has different expressions

17:48.720 --> 17:51.280
in different languages or even in the same language.

17:51.280 --> 17:52.880
Okay, this is an additional point,

17:52.880 --> 17:55.920
but Frege thinks that the same sense

17:55.920 --> 17:58.480
can be the meaning of different terms.

17:58.560 --> 18:01.600
It might be, I'm sort of playing a little fast

18:01.600 --> 18:05.200
and loose here, but it might be that Jay-Z

18:05.200 --> 18:08.640
and Hove, H-O-V, I'm pretty sure that's how it's spelled,

18:08.640 --> 18:10.240
those are two different names,

18:10.240 --> 18:12.560
but maybe they present him in the same way.

18:12.560 --> 18:15.600
So they have the same sense, two different names,

18:15.600 --> 18:17.120
same sense, same referent.

18:17.120 --> 18:19.120
That's also possible, Frege thinks.

18:19.120 --> 18:21.680
And then there's the case of what are today

18:21.680 --> 18:23.520
commonly called empty names.

18:23.520 --> 18:26.400
These are names that are meaningful,

18:26.400 --> 18:28.400
but they don't refer to anything.

18:28.400 --> 18:30.960
It may perhaps be granted that every grammatically

18:30.960 --> 18:33.920
well-formed expression representing a proper name

18:33.920 --> 18:35.520
always has a sense.

18:35.520 --> 18:38.400
This just means that if a name is meaningful,

18:38.400 --> 18:39.520
it has a sense.

18:39.520 --> 18:41.920
But this is not to say that to the sense,

18:41.920 --> 18:43.840
there also corresponds a referent.

18:43.840 --> 18:47.200
But just because a name is meaningful and has a sense

18:47.200 --> 18:49.920
doesn't mean that there really is an object in the world

18:49.920 --> 18:52.480
that is referred to by that name.

18:52.480 --> 18:55.280
Frege is going to give us an example right now.

18:55.280 --> 18:58.720
The words, the celestial body most distant from the earth

18:58.720 --> 19:00.640
have a sense, but it is very doubtful

19:00.640 --> 19:02.080
if they also have a referent.

19:02.080 --> 19:05.840
The phrase, the celestial body most distant from the earth,

19:05.840 --> 19:08.000
that's a perfectly meaningful label,

19:08.000 --> 19:10.400
it's a definite description, it has a meaning.

19:10.400 --> 19:12.480
Frege just thinks, and I think he's probably right,

19:12.480 --> 19:16.240
that there is no object in space that is the one object

19:16.240 --> 19:18.080
that is the farthest away from the earth.

19:18.080 --> 19:21.360
Maybe because like space curves or I don't know,

19:21.360 --> 19:24.000
but there might not be a thing out in the world

19:24.000 --> 19:25.280
that's referred to in that way,

19:25.280 --> 19:28.000
but nonetheless, the name can be meaningful.

19:28.000 --> 19:30.560
Here's another thing that's very important to Frege.

19:30.560 --> 19:35.120
It's important that the sense of a term is public.

19:35.120 --> 19:38.480
Different people can mean the same thing by a term,

19:38.480 --> 19:40.400
and so they have to be able to share the sense.

19:40.400 --> 19:43.440
And for that reason, the sense of a term,

19:43.440 --> 19:46.000
the mode of presentation contained in the name,

19:46.000 --> 19:47.840
blah, blah, blah, all of that,

19:47.840 --> 19:52.000
that's not the same as some private mental thing,

19:52.000 --> 19:54.640
some conception or image in your mind.

19:54.640 --> 19:58.160
It can't be that because that thing in your mind is private.

19:58.160 --> 20:02.240
No one else can see your conception can have it.

20:02.240 --> 20:05.040
And so whatever private stuff is going on in there,

20:05.040 --> 20:07.840
that can't be what Frege means by sense.

20:07.840 --> 20:09.840
The referent and sense of a sign

20:09.840 --> 20:12.960
are to be distinguished from the associated conception.

20:17.120 --> 20:21.760
The associated conception is whatever shows up in someone's mind

20:21.760 --> 20:24.640
when they hear this name, and Frege is saying,

20:24.640 --> 20:27.440
that is not the sense, and that's not the referent,

20:27.440 --> 20:28.880
that's some other thing.

20:28.880 --> 20:31.120
This constitutes an essential distinction

20:31.120 --> 20:33.520
between the conception and the sign's sense,

20:33.520 --> 20:35.440
which may be the common property of many,

20:35.440 --> 20:39.280
and therefore is not part or a mode of the individual mind.

20:39.280 --> 20:40.640
Frege's point there is simply

20:40.640 --> 20:43.840
that the sense of a term is common property.

20:43.840 --> 20:45.680
It's something that multiple people can share.

20:45.680 --> 20:47.600
And you can see why Frege thinks this.

20:48.320 --> 20:50.880
The sense is the meaning of the name,

20:50.960 --> 20:54.000
and he wants two different people to mean the exact same thing.

20:54.000 --> 20:56.640
If the meaning of a name was some private thing

20:56.640 --> 20:58.080
inside your own mind,

20:58.080 --> 21:00.320
then you could never mean the exact same thing

21:00.320 --> 21:02.160
by a term as someone else.

21:02.160 --> 21:04.880
This wasn't in the part of this paper that I've assigned,

21:04.880 --> 21:09.280
but Frege also thinks that the sense of a name or a term

21:09.280 --> 21:10.720
determines the referent.

21:10.720 --> 21:14.880
That is, why is this referent the referent of this name, right?

21:14.880 --> 21:17.200
Why is Jay-Z the name of this guy?

21:17.200 --> 21:20.160
Oh, well, it's because there's some description,

21:20.160 --> 21:21.120
there's some characterization,

21:21.120 --> 21:23.360
there's some mode of presentation of this guy

21:23.360 --> 21:24.800
that's associated with the name,

21:24.800 --> 21:27.280
and he meets that description.

21:27.280 --> 21:29.600
He fits that mode of presentation.

21:29.600 --> 21:31.280
Frege thinks something like that.

21:31.280 --> 21:34.400
Also, there's this famous telescope analogy

21:34.400 --> 21:36.800
that explains how all of these things are related,

21:36.800 --> 21:40.960
and I'm gonna use this in my picture of that.

