21:52.320 --> 21:54.640
I compare the moon itself to the referent.

21:54.640 --> 21:58.240
It is the object of the observation mediated by the real image

21:58.240 --> 22:01.840
projected by the object glass in the interior of the telescope

22:01.840 --> 22:04.000
and by the retinal image of the observer.

22:04.000 --> 22:06.160
The former, I compare to the sense,

22:06.160 --> 22:09.120
the latter to the conception or experience.

22:09.120 --> 22:12.480
Okay, so there's a person who's looking through a telescope

22:12.480 --> 22:13.840
and they see the moon,

22:13.840 --> 22:16.400
and there's three things involved here.

22:16.400 --> 22:20.400
There's the moon, there's the image of the moon

22:20.400 --> 22:23.600
on the piece of glass inside the telescope,

22:23.600 --> 22:27.120
and then there's the image on the inside of the person's eye

22:27.120 --> 22:28.000
on their retina.

22:28.000 --> 22:29.920
That's like the back of the eye or something.

22:29.920 --> 22:33.200
There's the image that is reflected inside their eyeball.

22:36.000 --> 22:38.560
The moon is analogous to the referent.

22:38.560 --> 22:40.880
It's the object out there in the world.

22:40.880 --> 22:43.680
The image on the inside of the telescope

22:43.680 --> 22:45.920
is analogous to the sense, right?

22:45.920 --> 22:47.920
Because a sense is a public thing,

22:47.920 --> 22:49.840
and different people could come

22:49.840 --> 22:50.960
and look through the telescope

22:50.960 --> 22:53.520
and they would see the very same image

22:53.520 --> 22:55.120
on the glass inside the telescope.

22:55.120 --> 22:56.480
It's not the object out there,

22:56.480 --> 22:57.840
but it's still something public

22:57.840 --> 22:59.760
that different people can interact with.

22:59.760 --> 23:01.280
It's common property.

23:01.280 --> 23:04.080
